# Naming Conventions

## Branding & Project Names

1. **Template defaults**
   - Product name: "FlowSync" (example - replace per project)
   - Domain: "flowsync.app" (example - replace per project)
   - Color theme: Blue primary (#3B82F6) - professional, trustworthy

2. **Regenerating branding**
   - Choose name that's:
     - Memorable and pronounceable
     - Available-looking domain (don't check, just generate)
     - Matches product category
   - Color palette should:
     - Have good contrast ratios
     - Work in dark mode
     - Not look like generic AI template

## Code Naming

- **Variables**: camelCase (`userName`, `isLoading`)
- **Functions**: camelCase, verb-based (`getUserData`, `handleSubmit`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (`UserProfile`, `SignInForm`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`API_BASE_URL`, `MAX_RETRIES`)
- **Types/Interfaces**: PascalCase (`UserData`, `ApiResponse`)
- **Files**: Match export (component file = component name)

## URL & Route Naming

- **Routes**: kebab-case (`/sign-in`, `/blog/post-title`)
- **API routes**: kebab-case (`/api/user-data`)
- **Query params**: camelCase (`?userId=123`)

## CSS Classes

- Use Tailwind utility classes (preferred)
- Custom classes: kebab-case (`.user-profile-card`)
- BEM only if necessary for complex components

## Anti-patterns

- Inconsistent naming (mixing camelCase and snake_case)
- Abbreviations that aren't obvious (`usr` instead of `user`)
- Generic names (`data`, `item`, `thing`)
- Hungarian notation (`strUserName`)
